						               													<description>La bataille des Alphamons is a simple simultaneous action selection game for two to 6 players. This game was designed to teach the alphabetical order to young children.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Start by making an alignment with the small alphabet cards that are numbered 1 to 26. This will be used as a reference: letter a will be the smallest and the z will be the highest card.&amp;#10;Deal 9 cards to each player. They all have a card printed on it. All players choose a card, then reveal them simultaneously. Use the reference cards to check witch card is the highest. The highest card wins the trick and take all the cards.&amp;#10;After 9 rounds, the one who has the most cards wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Alternate rule for older children:&amp;#10;If all the players are familiar with the alphabetical order, you can play with the following rules:&amp;#10;Each time someone makes a trick, the player that has revealed the lowest card can swap 2 cards in the alphabet.&amp;#10;When you have played all the cards in your hand, take the cards you have won to continue playing.&amp;#10;The game ends when one of the player has no more cards. The player who has the most cards wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
